5|$|He {{began his}} top-tier racing {{career in the}} IndyCar Series, making his <b>driving</b> debut during the 2000 season for PDM Racing. Hornish began <b>driving</b> for Panther Racing the {{following}} season, winning eleven races and the 2001 and 2002 series championships {{over the next three}} seasons. During the 2004 season Hornish began <b>driving</b> for Team Penske, winning eight more races (including the 2006 Indianapolis 500) and the 2006 series championship during his time with the team. When he left the series after the 2007 season, he held the record for most career wins in the series (19, broken by Scott Dixon in 2009).|$|E
5|$|In October 2010, Gascoigne {{was arrested}} for drink <b>driving.</b> He {{subsequently}} admitted being {{more than four times}} over the limit at Newcastle upon Tyne Magistrates Court. One day after being warned he could face a prison sentence for drink <b>driving,</b> Gascoigne {{was arrested for}} possession of cocaine. He should have appeared in court on 11 November to be sentenced for the drink <b>driving</b> offence, but instead he went into rehab on the south coast of England. He was given an eight-week suspended sentence on 9 December 2010.|$|E
