5|$|Sandusky {{included}} features {{designed by}} Thomas Rogers {{that had not}} been seen in locomotive construction to date. It was also the first locomotive to use cast iron <b>driving</b> wheels, and the wheels included built-in counterweights {{to reduce the amount of}} wear on the track caused by the weight of the <b>driving</b> rod and wheel all coming down at once during the wheels' rotations. Before Sanduskys construction, <b>driving</b> wheels were typically built with wooden spokes, much like wagon wheels. Some accounts also state that Sandusky was the first locomotive to feature a whistle, but this has since been proven false.|$|E
